Package com.teranpeterson.server.helpers

Class Generator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.teranpeterson.server.helpers.Generator
  • public class Generator
extends java.lang.Object
    Generates random ancestors and corresponding events for a user. Uses json files with names and locations to randomly generate location for the persons and events. Uses sudo random calculations to keep events in chronological order

    • Method Detail

      • generate

        public void generate​(java.lang.String username,
                     java.lang.String personID,
                     int numGenerations)
              throws DAOException
        Loads the current person and recursively adds specified number of generations. Each generation is approximately 23 years apart and uses sudo random numbers to add variability. Birth, marriage and death are generated for each new person
        Parameters:
        username - Username of user to create ancestors for
        personID - PersonID of user's person
        numGenerations - Number of generations back to go
        Throws:
        DAOException - Database exception

      • generatePerson

        private java.lang.String generatePerson​(java.lang.String gender,
                                        java.lang.String personID,
                                        java.lang.String spouseID,
                                        int year,
                                        int numGenerations)
                                 throws DAOException
        Recursive function that creates ancestors for a person. A person is created and a set of events are generated for that person. Recursively adds a mother and father to the created person. Adds everything to the database.
        Parameters:
        gender - Gender (m or f)
        personID - ID assigned by last iteration (used by spouse)
        spouseID - Spouse's id
        year - Current year to create events with
        numGenerations - Number of generations left to go
        Returns:
        ID of the person just created
        Throws:
        DAOException - Database exception

      • generateEvents

        private void generateEvents​(java.lang.String personID,
                            int year)
                     throws DAOException
        Creates a birth, marriage and death for a given person. Uses sudo random numbers to add variability to dates. Year is used to set location for marriage so that it matches for husband and wife.
        Parameters:
        personID - ID of person the event belongs to
        year - Current year to make events with
        Throws:
        DAOException - Database exception
